ildren who have parents who don't care and those parents who do care send there children to private school so they can get what they pay for ... and education.  I believe we need to have public schools but as a parent who cares,  I feel my children wasted 4 years in a system that just wanted to not leave chiildren behind so they offered classes in culinary arts, guitar, and parenting skills rather than English, Math and Science.  There is a saying... If you build it they will come.  Build a school designed to educate and hold parents accountable for the life skills. I don't pay my taxes for a babysitter. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="919" language="en" documentId="2699" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="neveragain282" date="Aug 29, 2013 8:27PM" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://living.msn.com/family-parenting/the-family-room-blog-post?post=ab228ffc-1e99-4b37-a7b8-0b6a4c3fb240" topic="public-private-schools" thumbsUp="16" thumbsDown="0" origId="2699" notes="" title="Is it wrong to send kids to private school?"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="919"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39"/></xmi:XMI>